        q: `A 66-year-old man has had a three-year history of cough and worsening shortness of breath. On physical examination, his pulse is 77 bpm and blood pressure is 110/80 mm Hg. Ejection fraction is normal and he does not have anginal pain. His liver span is increased to 14 cm. He has pitting edema to his knees. Jugular venous distention is noted to the angle of the jaw at a 45-degree elevation of his head while lying down. Which of the following is the most likely cause of his heart disease?`,
