        q: `A 41-year-old woman has been awakened at night with “air hunger” for the past year. She sleeps better when sitting up in bed. She does not have liver or spleen enlargement. Chest computed tomography scans suggest bilateral pulmonary edema. Her serum natriuretic peptide is &gt;400 pg/mL (very high). What cardiac disease best explains her presentation?`,
